ART. 89. Emergency Overtime Work. – Any employee may be required by the employer 
to perform overtime work in any of the following cases: 

(a) When the country is at war or when any other national or local emergency has been 
declared by the National Assembly75 or the Chief Executive; 

(b) When it is necessary to prevent loss of life or property or in case of imminent danger 
to public safety due to an actual or impending emergency in the locality caused by serious 
accidents, fire, flood, typhoon, earthquake, epidemic, or other disaster or calamity; 

(c) When there is urgent work to be performed on machines, installations, or 
equipment, in order to avoid serious loss or damage to the employer or some other cause of 
similar nature;

ART. 92. When Employer May Require Work on a Rest Day. – The employer may require 
his employees to work on any day: 

